	<ul class="article-footnotes__text accordion-content">
		<section id="footnotes" class="fn-group-container">
<ul class="fn-group">
<li id="FNa" class="fn"><a class="article-label">a</a> <span class="p">The detailed difference between water withdrawal and water consumption is presented in the section Water Withdrawal versus Water Consumption.</span></li>
<li id="FNb" class="fn"><a class="article-label">b</a> <span class="p">The scope definition of water usage<a class="reference-link xref xref-bibr" href="#B23" data-jats-ref-type="bibr" data-jats-rid="B23"><span class="sup">23</span></a> is in line with that of carbon emissions. Our scope-2 water withdrawal (and consumption when applicable) is for location-based electricity generation throughout the article. Large datacenters often adopt sustainability programs (for example, renewable purchasing agreements) to offset their location-based electricity usage and thus may have lower market-based carbon and water footprints.</span></li>
</ul>
</section>
	</ul>
